The paper deals with designing truthful mechanisms for online auctions with budgeted agents, which is a topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT) and computational social choice (cs.DS). The paper also involves designing efficient algorithms for allocation of divisible and indivisible items, which falls under the category of algorithms and complexity (cs.AI). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.TH) and machine learning (cs.LG).
